Global Short Glass Fiber Reinforced Polypropylene Market Insights
Short Glass Fiber Reinforced Polypropylene Market size was valued at USD 2.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.1 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.2% from 2024 to 2030.

Short Glass Fiber Reinforced Polypropylene Market Overview
The global Short Glass Fiber Reinforced Polypropylene (SGFR-PP) market size was valued at approximately USD 4.75 billion in 2023 and is expected to expand at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 7.1% from 2024 to 2030. This growth is attributed to the increasing demand for lightweight and high-strength materials in automotive, consumer goods, and construction sectors. The SGFR-PP market is experiencing rapid expansion, driven by its superior mechanical properties, including enhanced tensile strength and thermal stability, compared to unreinforced polypropylene. Furthermore, its ability to meet the stringent regulatory standards for automotive and industrial applications further fuels its adoption.

